  "description": "Minimal grayscale theme for Pi.",
  "readme": "# @codella/pi-theme-grayscale\n\nMinimal grayscale theme for [Pi](https://pi.dev): monochrome panels, soft silver borders, bright text, and clear contrast without color hue.\n\n## Install\n\n```bash\npi install npm:@codella/pi-theme-grayscale\n```\n\n## Use\n\nSelect `grayscale` in `/settings`, or add it to your Pi settings:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"theme\": \"grayscale\"\n}\n```\n\n## Package contents\n\n```text\nthemes/grayscale.json\n```\n\n## License\n\nMIT\n",
